うっとり(と)
うっとり(と) ﾛｰﾏ(uttori(to))
〔放心して〕 abstractedly; absentmindedly; vacantly; 〔恍惚(<sub>こ</sub><sub>うこ</sub><sub>つ</sub>)として〕 in a trance; in (a state of) ⌐ecstasy [rapture]; with rapt attention; spellbound.
▲うっとり(と)する　〔放心する〕 be absentminded; 《口》 be miles away; be in a world of one's own; 〔恍惚となる〕 be entranced; be enraptured; be transported; fall into a trance; be fascinated
・うっとり(と)した　〔放心した〕 vacant; blank; 〔恍惚とした〕 rapt; enraptured
・うっとり(と)したまなざし　《with》 a ⌐faraway [rapt, dreamy] look (in one's eyes)
・うっとり(と)した顔つき　a rapt expression.
▲彼は自分の花嫁をうっとり(と)眺めた.　He gazed at his bride with a dreamy look in his eyes.
・彼女はうっとり(と)夢見るような目をしていた.　She had a faraway, dreamy look in her eyes.
・その絶妙な調べにうっとり(と)聞きほれた.　I was completely ⌐entranced [enchanted] by the exquisite music.
